text.__SUMMARY__: Protea gaguedi is similar to Protea welwitschii and has hairless mature leaves and solitary flower heads. It is widely distributed in Africa, from Ethiopia to KwaZulu-Natal in South Africa.
text.References:
van Wyk, B. and van Wyk, P. 1997. Field Guide to trees of South Africa. Struik, Cape Town
Pooley, E. 2005. A Field Guide to Wild Flowers of Kwazulu-Natal and the Eastern Region. National Floral Publications Trust, Durban
